Description:
The application has a stock check feature that fetches data from an internal system.
Two weak anti-SSRF defenses are implemented, but they can be bypassed.

Objective:
-Access admin panel
-Delete user: carlos

Tools Used:
Burp Suite (Proxy, Repeater)

Exploitation Steps:
1️-Intercept Request
-Navigate to a product page
-Click Check Stock
-Intercept the request using Burp Suite

2️-Send to Repeater
-Forward the request to Burp Repeater
Locate parameter:
-stockApi

3️-Initial Attempt (Blocked)
-Modify the request:
-http://127.0.0.1/
Request is blocked due to SSRF protection

4️-Bypass Localhost Filter
Change the URL to:
http://127.1/

Successfully bypassed IP filtering
(Alternative representation of localhost)

5️-Access Admin Panel (Blocked Again)
Try:
http://127.1/admin

Blocked due to keyword filtering (admin)

6️-Bypass Keyword Filter
-Modify the path using case variation:
http://127.1/ADMIN
or:
http://127.1/aDmIn

Successfully bypassed keyword-based filter

7️-Delete User
Send final payload:
http://127.1/ADMIN/delete?username=carlos

Result:
-Bypassed weak SSRF defenses (IP + keyword filtering)
-Accessed admin panel
-Successfully deleted user carlos
